The paper proposes a framework for anonymizing personal medical data using generative adversarial networks (GANs). This involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with privacy concerns, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of medical data also suggests that the paper could belong to the databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques, which could be another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the ethical and legal implications of using personal medical data, which could place it in the cyberlaw and cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
